&lt;p&gt;Backed by Greylock and Y Combinator, fully remote since 2018.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;As a &lt;strong&gt;Senior Fullstack Engineer&lt;/strong&gt; at Postscript, you&#39;ll be a high-ownership contributor to one of our core product or platform teams — owning meaningful systems end-to-end, driving technical quality, and helping shape how we build across the organization. Our engineering teams operate at the intersection of scale and product velocity, which means you&#39;ll be working on distributed systems that matter to the business while also influencing the technical standards that allow Postscript to grow sustainably.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a high-autonomy role for engineers who are energized by ambiguity, take genuine ownership of their work, and bring a strong point of view on how to build things well — without sacrificing speed or pragmatism. AI isn&#39;t a nice-to-have here — it&#39;s central to how we work. We expect our engineers to be active practitioners of AI-first development: fluent with the latest agentic coding tools, curious about what&#39;s emerging, and constantly pushing the boundary of what&#39;s possible with AI in their day-to-day craft. If you&#39;re the kind of engineer who&#39;s already experimenting with new models and tooling before anyone asks you to, you&#39;ll feel at home here.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a senior engineer at Postscript, you’ll no longer be only writing code but orchestrating it.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This position is fully remote and can be based in the US or Canada.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
